## Severity
Critical
## Dimension
security
## Location
src/tools/lsp.rs:79-152
## Violation
`execute_lsp` accepts a model-supplied `file_path`, canonicalizes it, reads its contents into memory, then hands them to a language-server binary chosen by extension. NO check that the path is within a project root, NO denylist for system paths (`/etc/shadow`, `/proc/*/environ`, `~/.ssh/id_rsa`, `~/.aws/credentials`).

Quoted (lsp.rs:79-152):
```
    let Some(file_path) = args.get("file_path").and_then(|v| v.as_str()) else {
        return ("Error: file_path is required".to_string(), true);
    };
...
    let abs_path =
        std::fs::canonicalize(file_path).map_err(|e| format!("Cannot resolve path: {e}"))?;
...
    let content =
        std::fs::read_to_string(&abs_path).map_err(|e| format!("Cannot read file: {e}"))?;
```

Contents are sent over LSP to a child process; any LSP server can leak them. OWASP A01.
## Mandated refactor
1. Require `file_path` resolves under a configured project root.
2. Hard denylist for credential paths (`~/.ssh`, `~/.aws`, `/etc/shadow`, `/proc/*/environ`).
3. Cap file size before reading.
## Filed from QA review dispatch
